 Pro-Chancellor, Obafemi Awolowo University (OAU), Ile-Ife, Dr. Yemi Ogunbiyi (right); Minister of State for Power, Prince Goddy Agba; the university’s Vice Chancellor, Prof Eyitope Ogunbodede; Site Engineer, Ekop Udo; and Programme Manager, Savdagar Kangode, during the minister’s visit to the OAU power plant in Osun State…at the weekend.                                                                            PHOTO: NAJEEM RAHEEM  The assurance was given at the weekend by the Minister of State for Power, Prince Goddy Agba, during an assessment tour of the facility.When completed, the plant is to generate about 8.30 megawatts for the entire university community, including the sister institution, Obafemi Awolowo University Teaching Hospital Complex (OAUTHC).The minister stated that government was serious about the project and similar ones being executed in other federal universities across the federation. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .